entry.def: If you overpower someone, you manage to take hold of and keep hold of them, although they struggle a lot.

example.ex: It took ten guardsmen to overpower him...
The rebels were overpowered and arrested.
example.tran: 叛乱分子已被制服并拘捕起来。

entry.def: If a feeling overpowers you, it suddenly affects you very strongly.

example.ex: I was so overpowered by my guilt and my shame that I was unable to speak.
example.tran: 内疚和羞愧令我无地自容，难以启齿。

entry.def: In a sports match, when one team or player overpowers the other, they play much better than them and beat them easily.

example.ex: Britain's tennis No 1 yesterday overpowered American Brian Garrow 7-6, 6-3.
example.tran: 昨天，英国的头号网球选手以7比6和6比3轻取美国选手布赖恩·加罗。

entry.tran: （颜色、气味等）盖过，比…强烈得多
entry.def: If something such as a colour or flavour overpowers another colour or flavour, it is so strong that it makes the second one less noticeable.

example.ex: On fair skin, pale shades are delicate enough not to overpower your colouring.
example.tran: 浅色太阳镜色彩柔和，皮肤白皙的人戴上不会与肤色形成强烈的反差。

example.ex: Vegetables such as peppers can overpower the flavor of the stock.
example.tran: 像甜椒这样的蔬菜会抢了原汤的味道。
